al\">Download ‘Form NG (Notice and Grounds’ (PDF, 129KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>When you must appeal</h2>\n\n<p>For a conviction, you must appeal within 28 days of the date of your conviction - even if you were sentenced at a later date.</p>\n\n<p>If you only want to appeal against your sentence, the 28-day period starts from the date you were sentenced.</p>\n\n<h2>If you get permission to appeal</h2>\n\n<p>If permission is granted, your case will be reviewed by the Court of Appeal.</p>\n\n<p>A few weeks before the hearing you&rsquo;ll get a letter telling you where and when it is.</p>\n\n<h2>If you don&rsquo;t get permission to appeal</h2>\n\n<p>You will get a letter telling you that you can&rsquo;t appeal. </p>\n\n<p>You have the right to ‘renew’ your application and ask a &lsquo;full court&rsquo; of 3 judges to give you permission. The letter tells you how to do this.</p>\n\n<p>If you’re not given permission to appeal by the full court, you can contact the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.justice.gov.uk/about/criminal-cases-review-commission/forms-and-how-to-apply\" title=\"Criminal Cases Review Commission. \">Criminal Cases Review Commission.</a></p>\n\n<h2>The appeal decision</h2>\n\n<p>If you win your appeal against your conviction your sentence will no longer apply.</p>\n\n<p>If you win your appeal against your sentence it will be reduced.</p>\n\n<p>You may get any legal costs paid back (eg a solicitor&rsquo;s fee) and you may be able to get compensation.</p>\n\n<p>Use the form below to apply for compensation:</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.justice.gov.uk/downloads/compensation/compensation-wrongful-conviction.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Application for compensation for wrongful conviction form' (PDF, 201KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Application for compensation for wrongful conviction form’ (PDF, 201KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<p>If you lose your appeal, your original conviction will stay the same, but you may be able to appeal again. Get legal advice.</p>\n\n<h2>Stopping your appeal</h2>\n\n<p>You can stop your appeal at any time - download and use the form below.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/criminal/docs/crim-pr-form-part65-notice-of-abandonment-of-prosecution-appeal-s58-CJA-2003-coa-form-A-Pros.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Form A - Notice of abandonment of proceedings' - with guidance' (PDF, 22KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Form A - Notice of abandonment of proceedings’ - with guidance (PDF, 22KB) </a></p>\n</div>\n\n"}]},"updated_at":"2012-11-08T16:33:24+00:00","tags":[{"title":"Courts, sentencing and tribunals","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/justice%2Fcourts-sentencing-tribunals.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Attending courts, paying fines, appealing a sentence and tribunals","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=justice%2Fcourts-sentencing-tribunals","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/justice/courts-sentencing-tribunals"},"parent":{"title":"Crime, justice and the law","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/justice.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Legal processes, courts and the police","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=justice","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/justice"},"parent":null}}],"related":[{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/how-sentences-are-worked-out.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/how-sentences-are-worked-out","title":"How sentences are worked out","format":"answer","details":{"need_id":"484","business_proposition":false,"description":"If you are found guilty of a crime, your sentence will depend on a number of factors, including the type, seriousness and circumstances of the crime."},"updated_at":"2012-10-22T15:14:08+00:00"},{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/complain-about-low-crown-court-sentence.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.